meta {
  name: Compile
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/v1/kb-compile
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{accessToken}}
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "hint": "Extract preferences, decisions, and recurring patterns. Skip greetings.",
    "files": [
      {
        "path": "notes/2026-05-10.md",
        "contentType": "text/markdown",
        "text": "# Friday\n\n- Switched morning drink from coffee to jasmine tea — energy steadier.\n- Slept 7.6h last night. Want to track for a week.\n- Decided to use pgvector ivfflat index over hnsw for now (lower memory)."
      },
      {
        "path": "notes/diet.md",
        "contentType": "text/markdown",
        "text": "## Diet experiment\n\nNo refined sugar weekdays.\nReintroduce on weekends.\nTrack mood + energy in journal."
      }
    ]
  }
}

tests {
  test("status 200", function() {
    expect(res.status).to.equal(200);
  });
  test("returns written files", function() {
    expect(res.getBody().writtenFiles).to.be.an("array").with.lengthOf(2);
  });
  test("returns memories array", function() {
    expect(res.getBody().memories).to.be.an("array");
  });
  test("returns summary", function() {
    expect(res.getBody().summary).to.be.a("string");
  });
}

docs {
  Two-stage operation:

  1. **Write phase** — every file is sanitized + persisted under
     `<vault.rootPath>/tenants/<userID>/raw/<path>`. Same surface as
     `Vault/Upload Markdown`. Whitelisted extensions only. Each file
     capped at 10 MB; whole batch capped at 32 MB.

  2. **Compile phase** — text-shaped files are bundled and sent to the
     user's Hermes profile via `/v1/chat/completions`. The model has the
     `memory_upsert` tool exposed; it picks out distilled memories and
     calls the tool once per memory. Server persists each into pgvector
     scoped to the tenant. Loop terminates when Hermes returns plain
     content (the human-readable summary) or after 12 iterations.

   Image files are written to disk but do NOT enter the chat (Hermes
   gateway here is OpenAI-compatible chat, not vision). Use later for
   wiki rendering.

   Body shape:
   ```jsonc
   {
     "hint": "optional steering prompt",
     "files": [
       { "path": "notes/x.md", "contentType": "text/markdown", "text": "..." },
       { "path": "imgs/a.png", "contentType": "image/png", "base64": "..." }
     ]
   }
   ```
   `text` xor `base64`. Setting both → 400.
}
